 and garam masala then cook <b>5 min\/90°C\/speed <b>. Serve garnished with a drizzle of cream."}],"hintsAndTricks":["For a thicker dal, only add 100 g reserved cooking water in step 7.","This black lentil and kidney bean based Punjabi dish is served right across India. It is a rich vegetarian dish that can be served with bread or rice, or alongside other curries as part of a selection. Because of the lengthy total time (due to the soaking of the lentils and beans) this dish needs a bit of planning. It traditionally appears at weddings and parties."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","9h 30m","6 portions"]}